title: Navalny’s former chief of staff attacked with hammer outside Lithuania home
description: Leonid Volkov, former chief of staff of Kremlin critic Alexey Navalny, was attacked with a hammer outside his home on Tuesday.

title: A Ramadan of ‘sadness’ as war-weary Gazans go hungry
description: The Post spoke to Gazans in the north Tuesday about how they are marking Ramadan — and trying to survive — amid the chaos of war and a growing hunger crisis.

title: India to implement asylum law that excludes Muslims, as election nears
description: The citizenship law, which sparked riots after it passed in 2019, provides a naturalization fast track for persecuted non-Muslims from neighboring countries.

title: U.S. to send Ukraine $300 million arms package as further aid stalls
description: The arms package for Ukraine will be funded by cost savings from contracts the Pentagon brokered to replace previous weapons donations, the White House said.

title: As leader resigns, Haitian politicians rush to create a new government
description: Following Monday night’s resignation of Haitian Prime Minister Ariel Henry, the country’s leaders were given 24 hours to provide names for a transitional presidential council to lead the country.

title: Picasso tried to ruin his ex’s career. The Picasso Museum will show her art.
description: Françoise Gilot is thought to be the only woman to have left Pablo Picasso. Decades later, her work is on display in its own room of the Picasso Museum in Paris.

title: A ship carrying 200 tons of food is heading to Gaza. What to know.
description: A ship is bringing humanitarian aid to Gaza for the first time since the Israel-Hamas war began. José Andrés’s World Central Kitchen is operating the mission.

title: What’s happening in Haiti? Leader resigns as gang-led violence worsens.
description: Prime Minister Ariel Henry resigned as gangs tighten their grip on Haiti, leading to violence and food shortages. The U.S. pledged more financial aid.

title: Ukraine drones hit Russian oil facility as anti-Kremlin units stage attack
description: The drone strikes caused fires at petroleum facilities in Nizhny Novgorod, Russian media reported.

title: These are Hamas’s top leaders
description: The group has both a political and military wing. Some of its leaders are public figures while others operate in the shadows.

title: Andrew Tate and brother Tristan detained in Romania under U.K. warrant
description: Andrew Tate, the self-described misogynist influencer, was detained on charges that include allegations of “sexual aggression” in the U.K., his spokeswoman said.

title: France’s love of frog legs is contributing to species decline, experts warn
description: Over 500 scientists and veterinarians urged President Emmanuel Macron to help regulate the trade in frog legs, which are mostly imported from Indonesia.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Israeli strike targets Hamas commander; food shortage persists during Ramadan
description: Aid shortages and ongoing strikes have marked the start of the Muslim holy month, with little food available to break the daily Ramadan fast.

title: Haitian prime minister to resign, clearing way for new government
description: Ariel Henry will resign once a transitional presidential council is established and an interim leader is chosen, Caribbean Community leaders said.

title: Biden has huge leverage on Israel. He hasn’t really used it yet.
description: The United States is yet to threaten to withhold military aid from Israel. If Israel doesn’t work to lessen the humanitarian crisis in Gaza, that could change.
